<h1>Important Upcoming Policy Changes</h1>
<p>
  Before adding new farmers and products to our offering we need to change a couple of very important policies. We are planning to make these policy changes effective September 1, 2016. Please make sure you understand them before that date. Thanks and let us know if you have any questions or concerns! ~Farmer's Cellar
</p>
<h2>Updated Policies</h2>
<ol>
  <li><%= link_to "Monday night pickup deadline", how_things_work_url(anchor: "pickup_deadline") %></li>
  <li><%= link_to "Accidentally taking incorrect product", how_things_work_url(anchor: "incorrect_product_pickup") %></li>
</ol>
<p>------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>
Hello,
</p>

<p>
This is your Farmer's Cellar receipt for payment authorization #<%= @id %>.
</p>

<p>
Here is the product information for which you authorized payment:
</p>

<table border="1">
  <thead>
    <tr>		    
      <th align="left">ID</th>
      <th align="left">Producer</th>
      <th align="left">Product</th>
      <th align="left">Delivery Date</th>
      <th align="left">Price</th>
      <th align="center">Quantity</th>
      <th align="center">Sub Total</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <% @tote_items.each do |tote_item| %>
      <tr>
        <td align="left"><%= tote_item.id %></td>
        <td align="left"><%= tote_item.posting.user.farm_name %></td>
        <td align="left"><%= tote_item.posting.product.name %></td>
        <td align="center"><%= tote_item.posting.delivery_date.strftime("%A %b %d, %Y") %></td>
        <td align="left"><%= number_to_currency(tote_item.price) %> / <%= tote_item.posting.unit.name %></td>
        <td align="center"><%= tote_item.quantity %></td>
        <td align="center"><%= number_to_currency(get_gross_item(tote_item)) %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>

<% if @subscriptions %>

  <p>
    The total payment amount authorized for the products listed above is <%= number_to_currency(@amount) %>. Additionally, you authorized future charges to your payment account associated with the following <%= "subscription".pluralize(@subscriptions.count) %>:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <% @subscriptions.each do |subscription| %>
      <li><%= subscription.description %></li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>  

<% else %>

  <p>
    The total payment amount authorized is <%= number_to_currency(@amount) %>.
  </p>

<% end %>

<p>
Charges to your payment account will be made after products are delivered on your behalf. Keep in mind, however, that Farmer's Cellar cannot guarantee products will be delivered on your behalf. In that case your payment account will not be charged.
</p>

<p>
We'll email you again on each of the delivery dates listed above to let you know if product has been delivered for you or not.
</p>

<p>
Thanks!
</p>

<p>
Farmer's Cellar<br>
<%= link_to "www.farmerscellar.com", root_url %>
</p>